STRICT FILE OWNERSHIP: modify ONLY the files assigned to you below. Other agents are editing other files concurrently — touching a file outside your assignment corrupts the run. Never run 'git add/commit', never edit files under decree/ or src/ unless explicitly assigned. Follow repo conventions (CONTRIBUTING.md; match surrounding style).`

const TEST_COMMON = `${COMMON}
Test conventions (binding, from tests/CLAUDE.md and existing tests): module-level helpers (_write_config/_write_doc pattern from tests/test_sprint.py), all-zero-ULID ids (SPEC-00000000000000000000000001 style), monkeypatch.chdir(tmp_path), in-process <module>.run(argparse.Namespace(...)) with EVERY flag the parser defines defaulted, capsys + json.loads for output, assert exit codes 0/1 (2 where specified), model inspection via decree.sprints.load_view/validate_ledger. conftest has autouse reset_caches. Namespace builders for new subcommands must include every flag cli.py defines for them. When done run 'uv run ruff check tests/ --fix', 'uv run ruff format tests/' on YOUR files and 'uv run pytest -q <your files>' until fully green — report the final counts.`

phase('Tests')
const tests = [
