  },
  {
    key: 'T2-migrate-parallel',
    prompt: `${TEST_COMMON}

YOUR FILES (new): tests/test_sprint_migrate.py and tests/test_sprint_parallel.py ONLY.
tests/test_sprint_migrate.py — migration + v1 detection + store robustness: (a) dogfood-shaped v1 ledger fixture (closed sprint with carried_over [reason/to_sprint/snapshot] + completed [snapshot 100%] items, active sprint with a carryover item [carryover_from] + fresh items, non-empty backlog with review_after, non-empty draft_pool) -> migrate_sprint_ledger_run --apply: exit 0, ledger.yaml deleted, load_view equivalence field-by-field (incl. outcome snapshots/evidence, since/reason/review_after, carryover_from), validate_ledger clean; (b) --dry-run prints plan and writes NOTHING (directory snapshot identical); (c) guards exit 2: no v1 file, v2 already present, second --apply; (d) v1-detection: fresh project + fake ledger.yaml -> lint.run, sprint.run(status), new.run(spec) all exit 1 with 'sprint ledger v1 detected'; (e) malformed live file (non-mapping YAML) and filename/document mismatch -> validate_ledger error not crash; (f) fcntl lock: init/rollover acquire decree/sprints/.lock (monkeypatch fcntl.flock to record calls; pytest.importorskip('fcntl')).
tests/test_sprint_parallel.py — the parallel-development proof at the file level (no git): build project A (sprint init + one spec via new.run); shutil.copytree to B; in A create SPEC-A via new.run, in B create SPEC-B; union-copy B's NEW files (doc + live file) into A simulating a conflict-free merge (assert the two change-sets touch disjoint paths — that IS the invariant); lint.run in A green, both SPECs in default progress scope; then mid-sprint divergence: in A complete SPEC-A while in B (fresh copy of pre-complete A) rollover happens... keep it simple and deterministic: assert (1) disjoint-path property of two parallel creations, (2) union lints clean with both live, (3) two copies giving the SAME doc different scopes yields, after bringing both live files into one tree via distinct filenames, the filename/document-mismatch validation error (not a crash) — the git-level single-file conflict case is covered by the repo's e2e sim, not here. Also same-worktree concurrency: two sequential new.run calls in one project produce two independent live files; complete on one leaves the other byte-identical.`,
  },
  {
    key: 'T3-html-cli-map',
    prompt: `${TEST_COMMON}

YOUR FILES: tests/test_generate_html.py, tests/test_cli.py, tests/CLAUDE.md ONLY.
