    key: 'D1-usage-index',
    prompt: `${COMMON}

YOUR FILES: docs/usage.md and docs/index.md ONLY.
docs/usage.md: rewrite '### decree sprint' (lines ~209-246) for the v2 directory store — layout (state.yaml/live/closed), one-file-per-membership rationale (one sentence), full subcommand list now including 'decree sprint complete DOC-ID [--commit SHA]' and 'decree sprint drop DOC-ID --reason', updated pause semantics ('after every active item is completed, dropped, or rolled over'), rollover covering OPEN items only with pre-resolved items folding automatically, and a NEW short 'Parallel work with worktrees' subsection: each worktree's decree new/complete writes only its own files; merges are unions; an orchestrator supervises either by running decree in each worktree directory or by merging branches into an integration branch and running 'decree lint' there; rollover stays an integration-branch ceremony. Add '### decree migrate sprint-ledger' after the migrate governs section (~line 355): v1 single-file ledger -> v2 directory, --dry-run|--apply, --project, exit codes 0/1/2, 'run once per repository; git history preserves the old file'. Touch up '### decree progress' + '### decree ddd' (~268-310): default active scope excludes items resolved mid-sprint; --sprint <active-id> includes them. Touch up 'decree new' (~94-108) and 'decree generate-html' (~130-146) wording where it references the single ledger file. Use exact strings from ${FACTS}.
